# TypeScript / JavaScript Standards

## Runtime: `bun` Only

```bash
bun install               # install all dependencies
bun add <package>         # add dependency
bun add -d <package>      # add dev dependency
bun remove <package>      # remove dependency
bun run dev               # run dev server
bun run build             # build
bun run test              # run tests
bun x <tool>              # run a package binary (like npx)
```

**Never** use `npm`, `yarn`, `pnpm`, or `node` directly.

**One exception:** Directus extension scaffold requires `npx`:
```bash
npx create-directus-extension@latest   # only allowed use of npx
```

## TypeScript Config

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
    "exactOptionalPropertyTypes": true
  }
}
```

- No `any` — use `unknown` with type guards.
- Named exports preferred over default exports.
- Zod for runtime validation of API responses and form data.

## File Structure

- Max ~200 LOC per file. Split aggressively.
- Components in `src/components/<feature>/`. Shared primitives in `src/components/ui/`.
- Custom hooks in `src/hooks/`. Utilities in `src/lib/`.
- One component/hook/util per file.

## React / Next.js

- Next.js App Router (`app/`). Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when needed.
- Fetch in Server Components; use `unstable_cache` / `revalidatePath` for ISR patterns.
- Never `useEffect` for data fetching — use Server Components or SWR/React Query.

## Imports

- Use path aliases (`@/components/`, `@/lib/`) — configure in `tsconfig.json`.
- Absolute imports only (no `../../..` chains).
